I'm-- I-I am worried about you.

516
00:29:32.638 --> 00:29:34.941
-Don't... -She's only gonna
get worse. you know.

517
00:29:34.974 --> 00:29:36.308
I mean. i-it's progressive.

518
00:29:36.342 --> 00:29:39.278
Yes. I'm familiar with
what happens with Alzheimer's.

519
00:29:39.311 --> 00:29:40.612
I've done the reading.

520
00:29:40.646 --> 00:29:44.516
Yeah. well.

521
00:29:44.550 --> 00:29:48.320
-Read this.

522
00:29:48.354 --> 00:29:50.356
It's a brochure
for a memory care facility.

523
00:29:50.389 --> 00:29:53.025
I put Mom's name on a list.
and a room has opened up.

524
00:29:53.059 --> 00:29:55.494
You put her on a list
for a memory care facility

525
00:29:55.527 --> 00:29:56.963
without asking me?

526
00:29:56.996 --> 00:29:58.464
Because I knew
what you would say.

527
00:29:58.497 --> 00:30:00.132
You don't know
what I was gonna say.

528
00:30:00.166 --> 00:30:01.300
"I can handle this. Matt."

529
00:30:01.333 --> 00:30:02.801
Well. I can handle it. Matt.

530
00:30:02.835 --> 00:30:04.336
And I know you can
and you have been.

531
00:30:04.370 --> 00:30:06.973
and I don't tell you enough. but
you are a saint for doing it.

532
00:30:07.006 --> 00:30:08.975
I'm not a saint. I'm a daughter.

533
00:30:09.008 --> 00:30:11.543
A saintly daughter.
-Oh. come on.

534
00:30:11.577 --> 00:30:14.146
Who got the short end
of the stick

535
00:30:14.180 --> 00:30:16.148
because you're not married.
you don't have any kids.

536
00:30:16.182 --> 00:30:17.383
-It's not fair.
-Oh. my God.

537
00:30:17.416 --> 00:30:19.651
Stop it. No.
It's because I made a choice

538
00:30:19.685 --> 00:30:21.687
that I want to take care
of my mother. Okay?

539
00:30:21.720 --> 00:30:25.224
And-and I've never
complained about it. not once.

540
00:30:25.257 --> 00:30:27.726
Saints don't complain.
They suffer.

541
00:30:27.759 --> 00:30:29.228
I'm not suffering.

542
00:30:29.261 --> 00:30:31.830
This is my choice.
It's important to me.

543
00:30:31.864 --> 00:30:33.499
And. you know. I have the means.

544
00:30:33.532 --> 00:30:37.236
I have a really good job.
she gets benefits. you help out.

545
00:30:37.269 --> 00:30:38.504
-We're doing this.

546
00:30:38.537 --> 00:30:39.671
We're fine.

547
00:30:39.705 --> 00:30:41.840
But are you living?

548
00:30:41.874 --> 00:30:42.875
Matt.

549
00:30:42.909 --> 00:30:46.012
I mean it. Abby. It's just...

550
00:30:46.045 --> 00:30:47.679
You had something
with Tommy before.

551
00:30:47.713 --> 00:30:50.082
And ever since Mom has
been here. you've been alone.

552
00:30:50.116 --> 00:30:52.384
You got to start
thinking about yourself.

553
00:30:52.418 --> 00:30:54.686
And Mom's gonna need a facility
like this at some point.

554
00:30:54.720 --> 00:30:57.389
Just take a tour.
That's all I'm asking.

555
00:31:04.430 --> 00:31:05.864
It's been. like. 14 hours.

556
00:31:05.898 --> 00:31:09.535
How long's it take to pull a rod
out of a guy's skull. anyway?

557
00:31:09.568 --> 00:31:12.404
You ever heard of that saying.
"It ain't brain surgery"?

558
00:31:12.438 --> 00:31:14.406
Well. this is.

559
00:31:14.440 --> 00:31:17.043
What's 3 across
for when doubled in...?

560
00:31:17.076 --> 00:31:18.444
Just got off the phone
with the surgeon.

561
00:31:18.477 --> 00:31:21.280
-He's alive.

562
00:31:21.313 --> 00:31:24.883
-Yeah.

563
00:31:24.917 --> 00:31:26.585
Any... a

564
00:31:26.618 --> 00:31:28.955
There were some complications
when they took the rebar out.

565
00:31:28.988 --> 00:31:30.589
He started hemorrhaging.

566
00:31:30.622 --> 00:31:31.890
They got the bleeding
under control.

567
00:31:31.924 --> 00:31:33.926
but had to put him
in a medically induced coma.

568
00:31:33.960 --> 00:31:37.296
They'll let us know
if his condition changes.

569
00:31:37.329 --> 00:31:39.565
You mean if he wakes up.

570
00:31:42.801 --> 00:31:44.403
Or if he doesn't.

571
00:31:47.606 --> 00:31:49.075
Yeah.

572
00:32:19.705 --> 00:32:20.872
Buck. get the tools.

573
00:32:24.676 --> 00:32:26.178
Yo. Hen.

574
00:32:26.212 --> 00:32:28.447
Is it wrong I was stoked
there was an emergency?

575
00:32:28.480 --> 00:32:29.815
I was climbing the walls
back at the house.

576
00:32:29.848 --> 00:32:31.483
We all were.
and. yeah. it's wrong.

577
00:32:31.517 --> 00:32:33.152
We're not here to blow
off steam. We're here to help.

578
00:32:33.185 --> 00:32:34.620
Truck is registered
out of Texas.

579
00:32:34.653 --> 00:32:35.988
We're still looking
for the driver.

580
00:32:36.022 --> 00:32:37.423
It's got to be
over 100 degrees in there.

581
00:32:37.456 --> 00:32:38.524
Buck!

582
00:32:38.557 --> 00:32:39.858

583
00:32:49.335 --> 00:32:50.636

584
00:33:12.858 --> 00:33:14.860
-All right.

585
00:33:14.893 --> 00:33:16.328
get these people some water.

586
00:33:16.362 --> 00:33:18.164
I got him. I got him. I got him.

587
00:33:18.197 --> 00:33:20.232
All right. get these
people some water. come on.

588
00:33:20.266 --> 00:33:22.234
-Put it down. Hen. -BOBBY: All
right. this is truck 118.

589
00:33:22.268 --> 00:33:23.535
I'm gonna need as many
ambulances as we can.

590
00:33:23.569 --> 00:33:24.870
-Hurry up. come on.
-Chopper. too.

591
00:33:24.903 --> 00:33:26.072
We may have to medevac
a few of them.

592
00:33:30.209 --> 00:33:32.178
It's at least four and a half
hours to the Mexican border.

593
00:33:32.211 --> 00:33:33.745
if that's even
where they started.

594
00:33:33.779 --> 00:33:34.880
Come on.

595
00:33:34.913 --> 00:33:36.415
Ah. breathe.

596
00:33:36.448 --> 00:33:39.851
-Starting compressions.
-Go ahead.

597
00:33:39.885 --> 00:33:41.187
Get down.
all right. take it easy.

598
00:33:41.220 --> 00:33:42.354
All right. come on.
I know you can hear me.

599
00:33:42.388 --> 00:33:45.191
I need you to breathe for me.
okay

600
00:33:45.224 --> 00:33:46.392
Can you stand up?
Take my hand.

601
00:33:46.425 --> 00:33:47.926
Take my hand. Ready?

602
00:33:47.959 --> 00:33:50.229
-All right. go. go. go.

603
00:33:50.262 --> 00:33:51.930
Start helping 'em down. come on.

604
00:33:53.232 --> 00:33:55.367
Por favor. mijo.

605
00:33:55.401 --> 00:33:57.936
Come on. come on.
come on. come on.

606
00:33:57.969 --> 00:34:00.038
All right. give me something.

607
00:34:01.407 --> 00:34:03.041
-Ah!

608
00:34:03.075 --> 00:34:05.244
Javi. Javi. good job. good job.

609
00:34:05.277 --> 00:34:07.713
Uh. uh... to-to-todo bien.
todo bien. All right?

610
00:34:19.625 --> 00:34:21.893
BUCK: Here we go.
here we go. here we go.

611
00:34:21.927 --> 00:34:23.095
There you go.

612
00:34:24.963 --> 00:34:27.133
Here we go. here we go.
that's it.

613
00:34:27.166 --> 00:34:28.734
-Do me a favor.
please. please... -Hey!

614
00:34:28.767 --> 00:34:31.737
Dick! Where the hell
do you think you're going?

615
00:34:31.770 --> 00:34:33.439
Sick son of a bitch.

616
00:34:33.472 --> 00:34:35.574
Whole families
could have died in there.

617
00:34:35.607 --> 00:34:37.075
Someone with a badge and a gun

618
00:34:37.109 --> 00:34:39.645
want to put this trash
in custody

619
00:34:39.678 --> 00:34:41.079
Ooh. that was badass.
but I thought

620
00:34:41.113 --> 00:34:42.248
we weren't here
to blow off steam.

621
00:34:42.281 --> 00:34:44.650
You know what you can blow.

622
00:34:44.683 --> 00:34:46.518
Hen.

623
00:34:53.125 --> 00:34:54.826
Hey. uh. everything okay?

624
00:34:54.860 --> 00:34:57.095
You answered. You always answer.

625
00:34:57.129 --> 00:34:58.430
You're so sweet.

626
00:34:58.464 --> 00:34:59.831
Oh. no. everything's fine.

627
00:34:59.865 --> 00:35:01.667
Um. is this a bad time?

628
00:35:01.700 --> 00:35:03.769
Uh. no. I'm-I'm at a call.

629
00:35:03.802 --> 00:35:05.837
but I-I wanted to answer
and. you know. make sure...

630
00:35:05.871 --> 00:35:07.606
you're not out on the ledge
or something.

631
00:35:07.639 --> 00:35:08.807
Thank you.

632
00:35:08.840 --> 00:35:10.108
I can't believe
you're at a call.

633
00:35:10.142 --> 00:35:12.511
Um. I'm not on a ledge.

634
00:35:12.544 --> 00:35:16.014
But I'm in a windowsill.

635
00:35:16.047 --> 00:35:17.483
You're on a call.

636
00:35:17.516 --> 00:35:19.451
I'm letting you go.
Go back to work.

637
00:35:19.485 --> 00:35:20.819
We can talk later.

638
00:35:20.852 --> 00:35:22.321
Nah. come on. tell me.

639
00:35:22.354 --> 00:35:25.824
No. it's just my mom.

640
00:35:25.857 --> 00:35:27.859
My mom has Alzheimer's. did I
tell you that? I can't remember

641
00:35:27.893 --> 00:35:29.127
if I told you that or not.

642
00:35:29.161 --> 00:35:31.197
No. I. uh. I didn't know that.

643
00:35:31.230 --> 00:35:34.032
-Sorry.
-Um. thanks.

644
00:35:34.065 --> 00:35:36.302
And she's just...

645
00:35:36.335 --> 00:35:37.536
slipping. you know?

646
00:35:37.569 --> 00:35:39.171
She's getting worse. and I...

647
00:35:39.205 --> 00:35:41.640
I'm starting to feel

648
00:35:41.673 --> 00:35:42.874
like she might need more...

649
00:35:42.908 --> 00:35:45.844
than just me.

650
00:35:45.877 --> 00:35:47.813
More help. Professional help.

651
00:35:47.846 --> 00:35:49.515

652
00:35:49.548 --> 00:35:52.984
Yeah. Although
even as you say it out loud.

653
00:35:53.018 --> 00:35:55.654
I'm paralyzed with guilt
at the thought of it.

654
00:35:55.687 --> 00:35:57.256
I mean. she's my mom. Right?

655
00:35:58.357 --> 00:36:02.027
Yeah. that's rough.

656
00:36:02.060 --> 00:36:03.995
Look. I don't...
I don't know a lot.

657
00:36:04.029 --> 00:36:05.564
But if there's one thing
I learned

658
00:36:05.597 --> 00:36:07.999
over the last 24 hours.

659
00:36:08.033 --> 00:36:09.501
the only thing that matters

660
00:36:09.535 --> 00:36:10.669
is family.

661
00:36:10.702 --> 00:36:12.671
Right.

662
00:36:12.704 --> 00:36:14.573
Yes.

663
00:36:14.606 --> 00:36:17.075
You're so right.

664
00:36:17.108 --> 00:36:18.510
Thank you.

665
00:36:18.544 --> 00:36:21.179
Yeah. you got it.

666
00:36:21.213 --> 00:36:22.881
Um...

667
00:36:22.914 --> 00:36:25.784
Look. I'll talk
to you soon. Okay?

668
00:36:40.799 --> 00:36:43.402
Tatiana. I'm Bobby.

669
00:36:43.435 --> 00:36:44.870
We spoke on the phone.

670
00:36:44.903 --> 00:36:47.439
Oh. yeah. Hi.

671
00:36:49.441 --> 00:36:53.211
Now I know why Chimney
always calls you Gary Cooper.

672
00:36:53.245 --> 00:36:55.381
I see you've had some visitors.

673
00:36:55.414 --> 00:36:57.249
Yeah.

674
00:36:57.283 --> 00:37:00.386
All day and last night. too.

675
00:37:00.419 --> 00:37:03.422
Is that normal. or is Chimney
just really popular?

676
00:37:03.455 --> 00:37:05.056
Firefighters are a brotherhood.

677
00:37:05.090 --> 00:37:07.626
Cops are the same way.

678
00:37:07.659 --> 00:37:08.894
One of us goes down.

679
00:37:08.927 --> 00:37:10.061
we make sure
the family's looked after.

680
00:37:10.095 --> 00:37:12.631
And I'm the family?

681
00:37:12.664 --> 00:37:14.266
I was hoping to convince you

682
00:37:14.300 --> 00:37:15.934
to come to the hospital
to visit him.

683
00:37:18.103 --> 00:37:20.339
I thought you said
that he wasn't awake.

684
00:37:22.140 --> 00:37:23.742
They're bringing him
out of his coma now.

685
00:37:23.775 --> 00:37:25.110
It'd be good if you were there.

686
00:37:38.023 --> 00:37:39.991
He asked me to marry him.

687
00:37:40.025 --> 00:37:42.127
I know.

688
00:37:42.160 --> 00:37:44.262
It's not right. you know.

689
00:37:44.296 --> 00:37:46.765
Putting me
in that kind of situation.

690
00:37:46.798 --> 00:37:49.601
Either I say yes

691
00:37:49.635 --> 00:37:51.470
-or I'm some kind of monster.
-You don't have to say yes.

692
00:37:51.503 --> 00:37:52.938
You just have
to come hold his hand.

693
00:37:52.971 --> 00:37:55.841
This is not about love.
it's about decency.

694
00:37:55.874 --> 00:37:57.609
That's my point.

695
00:37:57.643 --> 00:38:00.278
Anything I do now that isn't
being Florence Nightingale.

696
00:38:00.312 --> 00:38:01.647
it makes me look
like some kind of jerk.

697
00:38:03.815 --> 00:38:07.619
So. I hold his hand
when he wakes up.

698
00:38:07.653 --> 00:38:11.122
Then it's stay with him
until he's out of the hospital.

699
00:38:11.156 --> 00:38:12.958
And then it's
you can't break up with him

700
00:38:12.991 --> 00:38:15.627
until he can walk or talk again.

701
00:38:15.661 --> 00:38:17.363
and that's assuming
that he ever can.

702
00:38:17.396 --> 00:38:18.964
And you want me

703
00:38:18.997 --> 00:38:21.367
to just play like I'm in love
for how long?

704
00:38:21.400 --> 00:38:23.301
A month

705
00:38:26.004 --> 00:38:29.207
I am not a bad person.

706
00:38:29.240 --> 00:38:31.877
-I am just not in love with him.
-Tatiana.

707
00:38:31.910 --> 00:38:34.513
My friend is coming out
of a medically induced coma.

708
00:38:36.181 --> 00:38:39.150
I don't know
if he'll ever fully wake up.

709
00:38:39.184 --> 00:38:42.320
And if he does. I don't know
if he's gonna be able to talk

710
00:38:42.354 --> 00:38:44.990
or see or hear
or even remember who I am.

711
00:38:45.023 --> 00:38:47.192
I am not asking you

712
00:38:47.225 --> 00:38:49.027
to love him or marry him.
and I'm not judging you

713
00:38:49.060 --> 00:38:50.328
for your feelings. I'm not.

714
00:38:50.362 --> 00:38:53.331
I'm just saying he loves you.

715
00:38:53.365 --> 00:38:55.000
Misguided as he may be.

716
00:38:55.033 --> 00:38:57.068
And the only two things

717
00:38:57.102 --> 00:38:59.170
I can think of to help him
are to pray

718
00:38:59.204 --> 00:39:02.007
and to hope
that if you're with him.

719
00:39:02.040 --> 00:39:05.010
he'll feel that love for you

720
00:39:05.043 --> 00:39:07.379
and it will give him a reason
to fight his way back to us.

721
00:39:09.548 --> 00:39:12.183
I'm sorry.

722
00:39:12.217 --> 00:39:14.620
I just can't.

723
00:39:23.094 --> 00:39:25.063
Okay.

724
00:39:25.096 --> 00:39:28.033
Um. she's had her midday pills.

725
00:39:28.066 --> 00:39:29.768
except I think I might have used

726
00:39:29.801 --> 00:39:31.870
next week's day-of-the-week box
by accident.

727
00:39:31.903 --> 00:39:33.371
Would you mind
just checking on that?

728
00:39:33.405 --> 00:39:35.407
-We'll get it squared away.
-Thank you.

729
00:39:37.943 --> 00:39:40.245
Am I about to be out of a job?

730
00:39:40.278 --> 00:39:42.380
Oh.

731
00:39:42.414 --> 00:39:44.215
-No. My brother left that.
- Oh. Oh.

732
00:39:44.249 --> 00:39:45.451
This is a good place.

733
00:39:45.484 --> 00:39:46.618
-Mm-hmm.

734
00:39:46.652 --> 00:39:49.087
-Vacancies are rare.
-Huh.

735
00:39:49.120 --> 00:39:51.723
Are you considering it?

736
00:39:51.757 --> 00:39:54.760
I was for a minute.

737
00:39:54.793 --> 00:39:56.127
But then I thought. you know.

738
00:39:56.161 --> 00:39:58.964
as long as my mom
is still here with me...

739
00:39:58.997 --> 00:40:01.733
I want her
to be here with me.

740
00:40:08.306 --> 00:40:10.442
We're going. we're going.

741
00:40:49.648 --> 00:40:51.116
He's a tough nut.

742
00:40:51.149 --> 00:40:53.118
He's gonna be in this room
for a few days.

743
00:40:53.151 --> 00:40:54.786
Intubation tube is out.
obviously.

744
00:40:54.820 --> 00:40:55.954
but the catheter's still in.

745
00:40:55.987 --> 00:40:57.789
Can he hear us?

746
00:40:57.823 --> 00:41:00.158
I always treat them
like they can.

747
00:41:00.191 --> 00:41:01.960
All right. two minutes.

748
00:41:01.993 --> 00:41:03.895
and then I'm kicking you out.

749
00:41:28.854 --> 00:41:30.756
Hey. Chim.

750
00:41:32.090 --> 00:41:34.526
We're all here for you. buddy.

751
00:41:41.032 --> 00:41:43.168
H-Hey.

752
00:41:43.201 --> 00:41:45.236
I-I was thinking maybe
when you come back to work.

753
00:41:45.270 --> 00:41:48.540
um. you know. you should do
The Maneuver instead of me.

754
00:41:51.710 --> 00:41:55.013
To motivate him to get better.

755
00:41:55.046 --> 00:41:56.514
He can't do The Maneuver.

756
00:41:56.548 --> 00:41:58.516
Yeah. he can.

757
00:41:58.550 --> 00:42:00.251
Hey. Chim.
you can do The Maneuver.

758
00:42:00.285 --> 00:42:02.220
Right?

759
00:42:06.457 --> 00:42:09.060
Chim.

760
00:42:09.094 --> 00:42:10.862
I. um...

761
00:42:10.896 --> 00:42:13.531
I tried to get ahold
of your parents.

762
00:42:15.266 --> 00:42:17.035
There's a 16-hour
time difference with Seoul.

763
00:42:17.068 --> 00:42:18.369
you know. so maybe...

764
00:42:18.403 --> 00:42:20.972
maybe that has something
to do with it.

765
00:42:29.915 --> 00:42:31.216
Yeah. it's all right.

766
00:42:32.317 --> 00:42:34.485
His family's right here.

767
00:42:44.095 --> 00:42:46.464
Please don't ever
let him do The Maneuver.

768
00:42:50.802 --> 00:42:52.738

769
00:43:34.112 --> 00:43:36.081
You've answered the call
on 9-1-1.

770
00:43:36.114 --> 00:43:38.750
Now here are a few more shows
to check out from Fox.

771
00:43:45.290 --> 00:43:47.826
My shows must be about life.

772
00:43:49.995 --> 00:43:52.297
